# üöó Mr. Cooper ‚Äî Ride Hailing System

A Python-based ride-hailing application simulating core features of a cab booking platform. The system handles customer ride requests, driver matching, fare calculation, trip management, and ratings.

---

## üìÅ Project Structure

```
Mr_cooper/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ main.py          # Entry point ‚Äî orchestrates the full ride flow
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Customer.py      # Customer class with ride request and payment methods
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ driver.py        # Driver class with online/offline and trip management
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ matching.py      # Nearest driver matching algorithm
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ trip.py          # Trip lifecycle management
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ fareengine.py    # Strategy pattern-based fare calculation engine
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ rating.py        # Rating and feedback system
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ README.md
```

---

## üîÑ System Workflow

```
Customer enters pickup & drop location
        ‚Üì
System finds nearest available driver (matching.py)
        ‚Üì
Trip is created and started (trip.py)
        ‚Üì
Customer can cancel or continue the ride
        ‚Üì
Fare is calculated based on ride type & conditions (fareengine.py)
        ‚Üì
Payment is processed using saved payment method
        ‚Üì
Customer rates the driver (rating.py)
```

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è Features

- **Driver Matching** ‚Äî Finds the nearest available driver within a search radius, expanding the search if none are found nearby
- **Fare Engine** ‚Äî Strategy pattern implementation supporting Economy, Premium, and No-Surge fare types
- **Surge Pricing** ‚Äî Automatically applies 2x or 3x multipliers during peak hours or bad weather
- **Trip Management** ‚Äî Full trip lifecycle: start, cancel, complete
- **Cancellation Fee** ‚Äî Charges a fee if the customer cancels after the driver has arrived (within 5 minutes)
- **Rating System** ‚Äî Customers can rate drivers after each trip; average ratings are tracked per driver
- **Payment Methods** ‚Äî Customers can add or remove saved payment methods

---

## üßÝ OOP Concepts Used

| Concept | Where Applied |
|---|---|
| **Encapsulation** | `CustomerPhase`, `Driver_phase`, `TripDetails` ‚Äî data and methods bundled in classes |
| **Inheritance** | `EconomyFare`, `PremiumFare`, `NoSurgeFare` inherit from abstract `FareStrategy` |
| **Polymorphism** | `calculate()` method behaves differently for each fare strategy |
| **Abstraction** | `FareStrategy` abstract base class defines the interface for all fare types |

---

## üí∞ Fare Calculation

| Type | Base Fare | Per KM | Per Minute |
|---|---|---|---|
| Economy | ‚Çπ30 | ‚Çπ12 | ‚Çπ2 |
| Premium | ‚Çπ50 | ‚Çπ18 | ‚Çπ3 |

- First 2 km are free
- Minimum fare: ‚Çπ60
- Peak hour surge: **2x**
- Bad weather surge: **2x**
- Both conditions: **3x**

---

## ‚ñ∂Ô∏è How to Run

```bash
python main.py
```

You will be prompted to enter:
1. Pickup coordinates (latitude & longitude)
2. Drop coordinates (latitude & longitude)
3. Ride type (`sedan` or `premium`)
4. Whether to cancel or continue the ride
5. Rating (1‚Äì5) and feedback after the trip

---

## üìå Sample Input

```
Enter pickup latitude: 40.7
Enter pickup longitude: -74.0
Enter drop latitude: 40.75
Enter drop longitude: -74.05
Enter ride type (sedan/premium): sedan
Do you want to cancel this ride? (yes/no): no
Enter rating (1-5): 5
Enter your feedback: Great ride!
```

